1
00:00:04,980 --> 00:00:10,280
 There's a movie about one's disappearance even from the afterlife

2
00:00:10,280 --> 00:00:15,680
 when no more people on the planet are alive to remember you.

3
00:00:15,680 --> 00:00:22,120
 Maybe life is all about memories.

4
00:00:23,180 --> 00:00:26,620
 Me in someone's memory,

5
00:00:27,590 --> 00:00:30,820
 or someone in my memory.

6
00:00:31,950 --> 00:00:34,380
 I think everyone lives

7
00:00:34,380 --> 00:00:39,860
 and breathes with different faces

8
00:00:39,860 --> 00:00:43,010
 in each memory..

9
00:00:47,310 --> 00:00:49,960
 Will I disappear?

10
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:53,770
 Or will I stay?

11
00:00:53,770 --> 00:00:59,640

12
00:01:01,060 --> 00:01:07,980

13
00:01:09,530 --> 00:01:12,320

14
00:01:17,190 --> 00:01:21,650

15
00:01:27,780 --> 00:01:30,050
Did you do that?

16
00:01:30,050 --> 00:01:33,580
- Sorry? 
 - Why did you take out Se Yeon's name?

17
00:01:33,580 --> 00:01:35,240
She's not here anymore.

18
00:01:35,240 --> 00:01:39,510
What? How can you say that?

19
00:01:39,510 --> 00:01:43,230
Why are you in such a hurry to remove her name?

20
00:01:43,230 --> 00:01:46,350
I'm not ready to send her yet.

21
00:01:47,880 --> 00:01:53,740
Why are you already treating her like someone who doesn't exist?

22
00:01:55,120 --> 00:01:59,480
I guess you'd remove my name immediately after I die, too.

23
00:01:59,480 --> 00:02:04,640
Since In Sook and I are disappearing soon.

24
00:02:04,640 --> 00:02:08,970
Why are you crying? It's not a sad thing.

25
00:02:08,970 --> 00:02:13,230
You're such a heartless person.

26
00:02:13,230 --> 00:02:18,070
How can you say that they're gone as if nothing's wrong?

27
00:02:18,070 --> 00:02:20,310
They're here.

28
00:02:30,200 --> 00:02:31,560
What is that?

29
00:02:31,560 --> 00:02:35,440
I... remember all

30
00:02:35,440 --> 00:02:41,390
these names and faces.

31
00:02:54,420 --> 00:02:58,930

32
00:02:58,930 --> 00:03:03,960
It's all in my memory.

33
00:03:04,790 --> 00:03:06,350
Even though they're not here.

34
00:03:06,350 --> 00:03:08,600
What is this?

35
00:03:08,600 --> 00:03:11,620
It's not even Death Note. 
  (Referring to the Japanese manga/anime)

36
00:03:30,810 --> 00:03:36,710
Unnie... how is your trip?

37
00:03:36,710 --> 00:03:40,120
Heaven is too far...

38
00:03:42,890 --> 00:03:46,290
so it takes a bit of time. Right?

39
00:04:08,250 --> 00:04:10,270
What is this?

40
00:05:28,780 --> 00:05:31,260
What should I do?

41
00:05:32,080 --> 00:05:34,420
What'll you do?

42
00:05:34,420 --> 00:05:37,370
Even for me, it's so hard and I'm in so much pain.

43
00:05:37,370 --> 00:05:43,170
What'll you do after you're left alone?

44
00:05:45,360 --> 00:05:49,240
I remember it so vividly.

45
00:05:50,500 --> 00:05:53,850
All the memories left in my heart

46
00:05:53,850 --> 00:05:56,570
are hurting me so.

47
00:05:59,230 --> 00:06:02,320
You're going to feel the same way.

48
00:06:02,320 --> 00:06:08,210
If I'm not there, you'll hold onto those...

49
00:06:10,580 --> 00:06:13,740
memories and suffer.

50
00:06:23,580 --> 00:06:25,700
I won't suffer.

51
00:06:28,890 --> 00:06:36,040
I'll pick one of those memories every day...

52
00:06:37,740 --> 00:06:44,610
and reflect on the best scenes.

53
00:06:44,610 --> 00:06:47,390
I'm going to cherish them.

54
00:06:47,390 --> 00:06:49,590
I'm going to enjoy it.

55
00:06:50,700 --> 00:06:52,920
Since it's mine.

56
00:07:11,950 --> 00:07:13,230
What is this?

57
00:07:13,230 --> 00:07:14,800
It's a billion won. Hurry up and post it.

58
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:18,490
This is Koo Ji Pyo's video and it's gone viral on the internet.

59
00:07:18,490 --> 00:07:20,940
Who uploaded it?

60
00:07:27,120 --> 00:07:28,510
Sung Mi Do.

61
00:07:28,510 --> 00:07:31,580
 -   
 -

62
00:07:31,580 --> 00:07:33,590

63
00:07:33,590 --> 00:07:36,130

64
00:07:36,130 --> 00:07:39,540
Are you okay?

65
00:07:39,540 --> 00:07:43,140
Was it... you?

66
00:07:51,790 --> 00:07:53,960
 What are you talking about?

67
00:07:53,960 --> 00:07:55,970
 Let's end it here.

68
00:07:55,970 --> 00:08:00,230
 The guy who killed Park Doo Jin is dead anyway. Then there's no evidence.

69
00:08:00,230 --> 00:08:03,700
 Let's not fight anymore and end it here.

70
00:08:03,700 --> 00:08:06,400
 I can't do that. I'll find the video.

71
00:08:06,400 --> 00:08:08,330
 That won't count as evidence for the murder.

72
00:08:08,330 --> 00:08:09,740
 But it's a motive for murder.

73
00:08:09,740 --> 00:08:11,390
 If Koo Ji Pyo gets caught...

74
00:08:11,390 --> 00:08:15,440
 the truth about how you received a murder request from him will come to light. There will be no way out for you then.

75
00:08:15,440 --> 00:08:21,060
 If I'm wrong, I'll handle it myself.

76
00:08:21,060 --> 00:08:25,150
You should've told me. Really.

77
00:08:25,150 --> 00:08:28,230
Then I could make my own decision.

78
00:08:28,230 --> 00:08:30,300
Why are you doing something stupid,

79
00:08:30,300 --> 00:08:33,980
like thinking by yourself and taking it upon yourself?

80
00:08:33,980 --> 00:08:36,420
Have you known it all along?

81
00:08:36,420 --> 00:08:38,420
I wanted to deny it.

82
00:08:38,420 --> 00:08:40,840
I didn't want to know.

83
00:08:41,670 --> 00:08:47,380
But when I got to know him, after facing it,

84
00:08:48,640 --> 00:08:51,190
it didn't hurt.

85
00:08:55,290 --> 00:08:56,810
 It was you.

86
00:08:56,810 --> 00:09:01,180
 Killing Park Doo Jin and letting them know about In Sook's whereabouts. It was all you.

87
00:09:01,180 --> 00:09:03,320
 Just to hide that one video.

88
00:09:03,320 --> 00:09:04,950
 Who said that?

89
00:09:04,950 --> 00:09:09,760
 Pyo In Sook? Min Woo Cheon? Do you really believe that?

90
00:09:09,760 --> 00:09:11,830
 Let me ask you one thing.

91
00:09:12,720 --> 00:09:15,100
 Were you at least sincere about me?

92
00:09:15,100 --> 00:09:18,620
 Or did you just want to use me?

93
00:09:18,620 --> 00:09:20,120
 Did you really love me?

94
00:09:20,120 --> 00:09:25,900
 Didn't you fall for me because I'm an heir and someone that everyone looks up to?

95
00:09:25,900 --> 00:09:29,160
 Fine. Being calculative is not a bad thing.

96
00:09:29,160 --> 00:09:31,550
 But you need to find the answer if you started it.

97
00:09:31,550 --> 00:09:36,940
 So if you just shut your mouth, I'll do whatever I can to get the situation under control.

98
00:09:38,560 --> 00:09:42,050
 You just need to wait a little more and we'll get a happy ending.

99
00:09:42,050 --> 00:09:44,310
 Happy ending, my foot.

100
00:09:44,310 --> 00:09:49,450
 Have you ever been hurt because of me?

101
00:09:49,450 --> 00:09:52,930
 You never once hurt because of me, right?

102
00:09:53,780 --> 00:09:56,250
 Neither have I.

103
00:09:56,250 --> 00:10:00,400
 It doesn't hurt as much as I thought it would.

104
00:10:02,050 --> 00:10:04,090
Why didn't you tell me?

105
00:10:04,090 --> 00:10:07,590
It was so pathetic till the end.

106
00:10:07,590 --> 00:10:11,400
Even my last love was so pathetic.

107
00:10:11,400 --> 00:10:13,990
No.

108
00:10:13,990 --> 00:10:18,250
I know that it's not my fault.

109
00:10:18,250 --> 00:10:23,410
I thought about it while sending Se Yeon.

110
00:10:23,410 --> 00:10:28,390
Everything I was holding was so light

111
00:10:28,390 --> 00:10:32,810
and wasted. That's why I let it go.

112
00:10:47,700 --> 00:10:49,940
Now is the time.

113
00:10:49,940 --> 00:10:52,830
We need to lock Koo Ji Pyo up and end this.

114
00:10:52,830 --> 00:10:55,090
But we can't find a single lead on Sin Tae Il's whereabouts.

115
00:10:55,090 --> 00:10:56,320
His phone is off, too.

116
00:10:56,320 --> 00:10:59,540
He'll start making a move, now that the video has gone viral.

117
00:10:59,540 --> 00:11:01,760
That won't be easy for him.

118
00:11:01,760 --> 00:11:04,110
There are eyes that are watching him.

119
00:11:04,110 --> 00:11:06,510
Although Koo Ji Pyo will probably insist it's not him.

120
00:11:06,510 --> 00:11:10,190
Tie him down with Narae's Cleaning's business transaction for now.

121
00:11:10,190 --> 00:11:14,660
I will confess. So use me to catch him.

122
00:11:14,660 --> 00:11:16,810
You can't do that yet.

123
00:11:21,010 --> 00:11:24,560
We have no evidence right now since Park Seung Sun is dead.

124
00:11:24,560 --> 00:11:26,570
For now...

125
00:11:31,340 --> 00:11:35,030
That person is alive.

126
00:11:35,560 --> 00:11:37,950
The man you showed me a picture of last time.

127
00:11:37,950 --> 00:11:40,610
I saw him.

128
00:11:40,610 --> 00:11:45,610
Ji Pyo handed over a bag of money to him.

129
00:11:45,610 --> 00:11:48,870
He probably threatened him with the video for it.

130
00:11:48,870 --> 00:11:52,270
Then we probably don't have much time now.

131
00:12:24,370 --> 00:12:26,800
You know it yourself.

132
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:30,010
My sins can't disappear.

133
00:12:31,550 --> 00:12:34,320
So I have to pay for it.

134
00:12:35,280 --> 00:12:38,840
- But— 
 - I know.

135
00:12:38,840 --> 00:12:43,210
The fact that it's now, hurts me a lot too.

136
00:12:46,500 --> 00:12:48,360
You can't.

137
00:12:49,180 --> 00:12:52,160
Not right now.

138
00:12:52,160 --> 00:12:54,670
You saved me.

139
00:12:56,100 --> 00:12:58,470
But I lived like that.

140
00:12:58,470 --> 00:13:01,670
Then you appeared in front of me again.

141
00:13:02,370 --> 00:13:06,240
That's why I got another chance.

142
00:13:06,240 --> 00:13:10,160
A chance to start anew.

143
00:13:34,950 --> 00:13:37,980
 A video that's gone viral on the internet has caused an uproar.

144
00:13:37,980 --> 00:13:41,450
Didn't I tell you? His energy wasn't good.

145
00:13:41,450 --> 00:13:44,980
Why is something that's newsworthy...

146
00:13:44,980 --> 00:13:49,710
happening to the kids in the Green Ray room.

147
00:13:50,700 --> 00:13:55,290
Why are you two lying around here instead of eating?

148
00:13:55,290 --> 00:13:57,280
I have no appetite these days.

149
00:13:57,280 --> 00:14:00,110
You still have to eat.

150
00:14:00,110 --> 00:14:03,870
- It'll go away once you eat. 
 - You shouldn't skip meals yourself.

151
00:14:03,870 --> 00:14:05,900
- You've gotten skinny. 
 - Gosh.

152
00:14:07,830 --> 00:14:10,590
Why aren't you ladies getting surgery?

153
00:14:10,590 --> 00:14:12,800
There's chemo, too.

154
00:14:12,800 --> 00:14:14,440
I relapsed.

155
00:14:14,440 --> 00:14:18,020
Once it did, I figured what's the point of doing more.

156
00:14:18,020 --> 00:14:19,910
They told me I'm inoperable.

157
00:14:19,910 --> 00:14:21,970
No, they said they won't operate on me.

158
00:14:21,970 --> 00:14:23,800
Isn't In Sook the same case as me?

159
00:14:23,800 --> 00:14:25,780
They said her chances are low.

160
00:14:25,780 --> 00:14:28,350
She was told that operation may be more dangerous,

161
00:14:28,350 --> 00:14:30,100
so they said she can't.

162
00:14:30,100 --> 00:14:32,180
I looked around...

163
00:14:32,180 --> 00:14:35,910
when one place asked if she'd like to try.

164
00:14:35,910 --> 00:14:39,230
But they can't guarantee anything either.

165
00:14:39,230 --> 00:14:42,090
- You're not being scammed again, are you? 
 - Gosh.

166
00:14:42,090 --> 00:14:43,980
Don't say that.

167
00:14:43,980 --> 00:14:47,200
But In Sook won't even let me talk to them.

168
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:49,620
I'm scared, too.

169
00:14:49,620 --> 00:14:54,480
If she dies during surgery, I'm afraid it'll haunt me forever.

170
00:14:54,480 --> 00:14:57,130
I also wonder if it's right...

171
00:14:57,130 --> 00:15:01,340
for her to spend her remaining time in pain like that.

172
00:15:02,900 --> 00:15:04,920
Nor do we have the money.

173
00:15:04,920 --> 00:15:06,730
Gosh, isn't it strange?

174
00:15:06,730 --> 00:15:11,290
That people need money even in a life or death situation?

175
00:15:23,860 --> 00:15:26,270
Can you step out for a moment?

176
00:15:39,380 --> 00:15:42,500
- Why did you come to work? 
 - Father.

177
00:15:42,500 --> 00:15:46,410
Help me. It's not like that video can prove anything.

178
00:15:46,410 --> 00:15:49,740
There's definitely a way for me to get out. You're good at it!

179
00:15:49,740 --> 00:15:52,220
Something minor just blew up.

180
00:15:52,220 --> 00:15:55,300
I tried to stop it myself, but...

181
00:15:55,300 --> 00:15:58,210
You killed a person.

182
00:15:58,210 --> 00:16:00,430
You thought I didn't know anything?

183
00:16:00,430 --> 00:16:04,250
You crossed the line. Do I have to cross it, too?

184
00:16:04,250 --> 00:16:06,740
Father, all of this...

185
00:16:06,740 --> 00:16:09,130
it's all your fault in the end! Your fault!

186
00:16:09,130 --> 00:16:10,430
Shut up!

187
00:16:10,430 --> 00:16:13,250
The most stupid guy in the world is one that blames his parents.

188
00:16:13,250 --> 00:16:15,020
I always told you.

189
00:16:15,020 --> 00:16:18,890
Don't try to benefit from your parents or try to blame them.

190
00:16:18,890 --> 00:16:21,450
I said I don't need that kind of child!

191
00:16:48,350 --> 00:16:50,640
Did I do the right thing?

192
00:16:53,500 --> 00:16:58,420
If Ji Pyo gets caught, Woo Cheon will get involved, too. Right?

193
00:16:59,550 --> 00:17:01,280
How strange.

194
00:17:01,280 --> 00:17:04,090
Why do I keep making you suffer?

195
00:17:04,090 --> 00:17:06,640
What was our relationship in our past lives?

196
00:17:07,450 --> 00:17:09,430
Romantic rivals.

197
00:17:10,610 --> 00:17:12,290
Romantic rivals?

198
00:17:12,290 --> 00:17:15,620
Hey, you think you're even a match for me?

199
00:17:15,620 --> 00:17:18,600
- What, so we're fighting for Woo Cheon then? 
 - Yes.

200
00:17:18,600 --> 00:17:20,270
I won.

201
00:17:20,270 --> 00:17:24,270
Which is why you held a grudge and appeared in this life—

202
00:17:24,270 --> 00:17:29,300
What are you saying? Regardless, you two are a match made in heaven.

203
00:17:29,300 --> 00:17:32,720
Think about it. We all met together at first.

204
00:17:32,720 --> 00:17:36,360
The fact that he fell for you instead of me...

205
00:17:36,360 --> 00:17:39,270
it means that's true love.

206
00:17:39,270 --> 00:17:43,190
So, in the next life...

207
00:17:45,880 --> 00:17:50,100
there's no such thing as a next life. I don't believe in that.

208
00:17:51,610 --> 00:17:55,430
Which is why, you have to do everything in this life.

209
00:17:55,430 --> 00:17:57,390
Okay?

210
00:17:58,410 --> 00:18:00,660
Do everything! Okay?

211
00:18:21,950 --> 00:18:25,890
- I thought we were going to go watch a movie. 
 - We are watching a movie.

212
00:18:25,890 --> 00:18:30,140
Do we really have to watch something so bloody with all the killing?

213
00:18:30,140 --> 00:18:32,950
There are romantic movies and stuff, too.

214
00:18:32,950 --> 00:18:35,280
Why would we watch other people dating?

215
00:18:35,280 --> 00:18:37,540
We're doing it ourselves.

216
00:19:19,310 --> 00:19:24,350
What about Koo Ji Pyo? The guy who took the fall as the administrator of Hello Video already served his time and got out.

217
00:19:24,350 --> 00:19:26,220
Would he speak the truth now when he's probably received money from him?

218
00:19:26,220 --> 00:19:30,470
It's not over. The US Ministry of Justice requested his extradition.

219
00:19:30,470 --> 00:19:34,370
You think he'd go to the US and serve a hundred-year sentence or confess to us?

220
00:19:34,370 --> 00:19:36,560
What about Park Seung Sun?

221
00:19:36,560 --> 00:19:40,110
- Did the henchmen give you anything? 
 - Yes, he's in Korea now.

222
00:19:40,110 --> 00:19:42,230
I think he's moving with Sin Tae Il.

223
00:19:42,230 --> 00:19:44,000
Koo Ji Pyo will make a move.

224
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:49,120
No. I've blocked it so that he can't even approach them.

225
00:19:59,390 --> 00:20:01,140
What is this, Park Seung Sun?

226
00:20:01,140 --> 00:20:02,840
They have a lead on us.

227
00:20:02,840 --> 00:20:06,140
I think I'll have to ride on that private plane.

228
00:20:07,070 --> 00:20:08,890
We're one body from now, all right?

229
00:20:08,890 --> 00:20:12,280
- What about Sin Tae Il? 
 - I don't know. He didn't come at our promised time.

230
00:20:12,280 --> 00:20:14,590
He probably got caught already.

231
00:20:14,590 --> 00:20:17,340
- Hey, let's go. 
 - Why would I go with you?

232
00:20:17,340 --> 00:20:21,060
- We're in this mess because of you, you bastard! 
 - How dare you to call me that, you bastard!

233
00:20:21,060 --> 00:20:23,010
And why is this all because of me? It's because of you!

234
00:20:23,010 --> 00:20:25,490
Why did you screw up and kill someone?

235
00:20:25,490 --> 00:20:28,530
Think about it a little if you have a brain.

236
00:20:28,530 --> 00:20:31,180
You're the worst scumbag out of everyone.

237
00:21:08,980 --> 00:21:11,520
Why are you acting different? You're scaring me.

238
00:21:11,520 --> 00:21:15,700
The sunlight hit you for five seconds and you looked really handsome.

239
00:21:15,700 --> 00:21:18,690
- Five seconds? 
 - Yes.

240
00:21:18,690 --> 00:21:20,600
What about now?

241
00:21:36,070 --> 00:21:42,080
Never in my life did you feed me food.

242
00:21:46,560 --> 00:21:48,720
You smile so well, too.

243
00:21:48,720 --> 00:21:53,320
How did you live all your life without smiling when you're that good at it?

244
00:21:57,850 --> 00:22:00,080
Here.

245
00:22:00,080 --> 00:22:01,980
You too.

246
00:22:06,510 --> 00:22:09,550
Why did you offer to dye my hair all of a sudden?

247
00:22:09,550 --> 00:22:11,600
You used to ask me to dye it in the past.

248
00:22:11,600 --> 00:22:15,020
- You hated it. 
 - I didn't like it then.

249
00:22:15,020 --> 00:22:16,150
Didn't like what?

250
00:22:16,150 --> 00:22:19,010
I didn't get why you had to dye your gray hair black.

251
00:22:19,010 --> 00:22:23,290
I didn't like how all the grandmas had the same dyed hair.

252
00:22:24,300 --> 00:22:28,230
It's because we don't like that people can see all the time that has passed.

253
00:22:28,230 --> 00:22:32,280
We don't like the time passing.

254
00:22:32,280 --> 00:22:33,690
Why?

255
00:22:33,690 --> 00:22:37,140
It's time that you survived for so long.

256
00:22:37,140 --> 00:22:40,440
It shows those times.

257
00:22:40,440 --> 00:22:43,510
Right. You are right.

258
00:22:43,510 --> 00:22:47,570
They are those times, but we try to erase them.

259
00:22:47,570 --> 00:22:55,520
I want to walk around gray-haired with In Sook later when I'm old.

260
00:22:55,520 --> 00:22:57,610
All gray.

261
00:22:57,610 --> 00:22:59,910
Until your roots turn gray?

262
00:22:59,910 --> 00:23:02,700
Oh, that's what that meant.

263
00:23:02,700 --> 00:23:10,010
I... once... tried to die.

264
00:23:10,010 --> 00:23:13,470
Life was too tough.

265
00:23:13,470 --> 00:23:16,860
No matter how much I tried, it just didn't work out.

266
00:23:16,860 --> 00:23:21,650
One day, I stood blankly by a river.

267
00:23:21,650 --> 00:23:24,870
Next thing, I was walking in with my shoes off.

268
00:23:24,870 --> 00:23:31,850
But suddenly, your father Gang Sun's face popped up.

269
00:23:31,850 --> 00:23:36,990
I couldn't die once that face popped up.

270
00:23:36,990 --> 00:23:39,740
So I survived it.

271
00:23:39,740 --> 00:23:42,980
That is life for everyone.

272
00:23:43,940 --> 00:23:49,010
You live for others. You live because of others.

273
00:23:49,010 --> 00:23:54,950
When I see the two of you together and smiling like this...

274
00:23:54,950 --> 00:23:58,000
it wears my heart out.

275
00:23:58,000 --> 00:24:01,480
- In Sook. 
 - Yes?

276
00:24:07,100 --> 00:24:11,210
You should live like that, too. Live for others.

277
00:24:11,210 --> 00:24:14,850
Look at him. Take a look at his eyes.

278
00:24:14,850 --> 00:24:17,190
Live for Woo Cheon.

279
00:24:17,190 --> 00:24:20,710
Try getting surgery and try out chemo, too.

280
00:24:20,710 --> 00:24:22,340
Grandma, that's—

281
00:24:22,340 --> 00:24:27,470
I know! It's scary. You don't know if the surgery could go wrong.

282
00:24:27,470 --> 00:24:31,380
You get the surgery, only to be told that your condition is worse.

283
00:24:31,380 --> 00:24:33,590
But let's still try.

284
00:24:33,590 --> 00:24:37,390
We're just trying something new. No big deal!

285
00:24:37,390 --> 00:24:42,310
Let's try. Let's try whatever we can.

286
00:24:42,310 --> 00:24:46,980
Grandma Cheon Deok gave us money. She gave us a big amount.

287
00:24:46,980 --> 00:24:51,540
She wants you to try what she couldn't.

288
00:24:51,540 --> 00:24:55,130
It's shameless of me, but I'm going to take that money.

289
00:24:55,130 --> 00:24:57,630
If that means you can get better...

290
00:24:57,630 --> 00:25:02,030
I'm going to work until my back breaks and pay her back.

291
00:25:02,030 --> 00:25:06,910
As long as I have you... if I have you...

292
00:25:06,910 --> 00:25:10,350
I can do anything.

293
00:25:12,000 --> 00:25:13,650
Okay?

294
00:25:32,620 --> 00:25:34,930

295
00:25:40,830 --> 00:25:43,070
It's over.

296
00:25:43,070 --> 00:25:44,820
It's all over now.

297
00:25:44,820 --> 00:25:46,730
It's done.

298
00:25:51,720 --> 00:25:54,190
This is the last time, Woo Cheon.

299
00:25:54,860 --> 00:25:56,750

300
00:25:56,750 --> 00:26:00,280

301
