00:27:05,160 --> 00:27:06,800
Yes.

314
00:27:15,760 --> 00:27:18,080
What should we do?

315
00:27:18,080 --> 00:27:20,800
What should we?

316
00:27:20,800 --> 00:27:23,340
What can we do?

317
00:27:25,790 --> 00:27:27,690
Whatever.

318
00:27:35,650 --> 00:27:38,060
Shall we run away?

319
00:27:39,070 --> 00:27:41,400
No.

320
00:27:41,400 --> 00:27:43,360
Then?

321
00:27:44,360 --> 00:27:46,660
Let's go to my house.

322
00:27:59,390 --> 00:28:02,620
This is what your room looks like.

323
00:28:03,910 --> 00:28:08,220
Yes. You are the first.

324
00:28:08,220 --> 00:28:11,260
Nobody else ever came.

325
00:28:16,570 --> 00:28:18,510
This...

326
00:28:21,350 --> 00:28:23,210
I brought it.

327
00:28:23,210 --> 00:28:24,210
When?

328
00:28:24,210 --> 00:28:27,430
It's yours, so I wanted you to sit on it.

329
00:28:27,430 --> 00:28:29,970
So you can sit and rest.

330
00:28:31,080 --> 00:28:33,360
- Sit down. 
 - Okay.

331
00:28:47,970 --> 00:28:51,470
I guess you never cooked anything before?

332
00:28:51,470 --> 00:28:57,100
No. This place felt like a prison.

333
00:28:57,100 --> 00:29:02,140
But it's different with you over there.

334
00:29:02,140 --> 00:29:04,670
Everything is changing.

335
00:29:13,440 --> 00:29:16,770
Take a good look while you wait.

336
00:29:16,770 --> 00:29:18,360
Okay.

337
00:30:16,980 --> 00:30:20,620
It would be nice for you to grow a plant.

338
00:30:20,620 --> 00:30:26,120
This place gets a lot of sunlight, so it'll grow well.

339
00:30:27,020 --> 00:30:32,820
 I lived with the curtains closed all the time, so I didn't know.

340
00:30:37,040 --> 00:30:40,220
Shall we hang our picture, too?

341
00:30:40,220 --> 00:30:43,530
 Even if it's a little silly.

342
00:30:44,400 --> 00:30:48,290
 White for the blankets.

343
00:30:48,290 --> 00:30:53,430
 My grandma didn't like white. She said it was hard to wash.

344
00:30:53,430 --> 00:30:56,870
 That's why everything was colorful and drab.

345
00:30:56,870 --> 00:31:01,370
 I'm going to get a very white blanket.

346
00:31:02,290 --> 00:31:05,740
Then we'll get matching white pajamas.

347
00:31:07,630 --> 00:31:11,170
 Whenever we wake up in the morning...

348
00:31:12,090 --> 00:31:14,900
 you'll be in front of my eyes.

349
00:31:43,160 --> 00:31:45,700
What is all this?

350
00:31:47,210 --> 00:31:48,510
In Sook isn't here.

351
00:31:48,510 --> 00:31:50,050
I know!

352
00:31:50,050 --> 00:31:53,510
- I brought it for you. 
 - Gosh!

353
00:31:53,510 --> 00:31:54,940
- It looks delicious. 
 - My goodness.

354
00:31:54,940 --> 00:31:58,060
Me and you. We do this because there's a void.

355
00:31:58,060 --> 00:32:00,760
That's why we gather everything we can.

356
00:32:00,760 --> 00:32:06,000
I pick up trash and you buy whatever you can.

357
00:32:10,980 --> 00:32:14,640
- It's hot! Gosh, it's hot. 
 - My goodness.

358
00:32:14,640 --> 00:32:17,620
- Gosh, your temper. 
 - What?

359
00:32:17,620 --> 00:32:19,130
That's my name.

360
00:32:19,130 --> 00:32:22,030
- Sung Mi Do? 
 - Yes. 
  (T/N: Sung Mi Do sounds like the word for "temper")

361
00:32:22,030 --> 00:32:23,660
Is that so?

362
00:32:26,790 --> 00:32:29,790
This is really delicious! What kimchi did you use to make it?

363
00:32:29,790 --> 00:32:33,120
What else? I used my kimchi.

364
00:32:33,120 --> 00:32:36,770
I like pajeon, too. Can't you make me that, too?

365
00:32:36,770 --> 00:32:40,700
How are you the polar opposite of In Sook?

366
00:32:40,700 --> 00:32:43,710
Every person is different.

367
00:32:43,710 --> 00:32:48,350
If you were my granddaughter, it would've been easier mentally.

368
00:32:48,350 --> 00:32:53,220
You just yell and talk about everything.

369
00:32:56,520 --> 00:33:02,360
But I never did that with my mom either.

370
00:33:11,160 --> 00:33:16,500
You're not going to try to get surgery or anything?

371
00:33:16,500 --> 00:33:20,190
Well, I tried.

372
00:33:20,190 --> 00:33:23,780
I went to all sorts of places every day.

373
00:33:23,780 --> 00:33:27,550
One hospital today and another tomorrow.

374
00:33:27,550 --> 00:33:31,260
But they all said they couldn't.

375
00:33:33,690 --> 00:33:38,990
Grandma, I want to live too.

376
00:33:40,040 --> 00:33:43,860
All humans feel that way.

377
00:33:43,860 --> 00:33:46,960
But they said I couldn't.

378
00:33:48,270 --> 00:33:51,030
If they say that...

379
00:34:07,580 --> 00:34:10,070
I want to live, too.

380
00:34:13,870 --> 00:34:16,650
You pretty thing.

381
00:34:17,860 --> 00:34:20,070
Thank you.

382
00:34:33,100 --> 00:34:38,950
Every person has at least one person.

383
00:34:38,950 --> 00:34:42,450
But I didn't have one.

384
00:34:42,450 --> 00:34:44,790
I was always alone.

385
00:34:46,820 --> 00:34:50,160
That felt so normal.

386
00:34:51,500 --> 00:34:57,230
So I wasn't lonely. But I was wrong.

387
00:34:59,050 --> 00:35:02,630
I bought a big teddy bear one day.

388
00:35:10,680 --> 00:35:13,280

389
00:35:13,280 --> 00:35:15,570
But I threw it away.

390
00:35:17,060 --> 00:35:20,260
Because I didn't like how I was feeling lonely.

391
00:35:35,630 --> 00:35:37,740
Is it...

392
00:35:43,060 --> 00:35:45,830
Did you ever think this?

393
00:35:46,660 --> 00:35:50,220
How often coincidences are repeated...

394
00:35:50,220 --> 00:35:53,720
for us to meet the one.

395
00:35:53,720 --> 00:35:57,900
 Why do you pick this stuff up?

396
00:35:57,900 --> 00:36:02,200
Maybe they meet against all the odds.

397
00:36:02,200 --> 00:36:06,630
The thought that that's how you become the one for one another.

398
00:36:08,120 --> 00:36:13,940
Maybe life can only be saved by that one and only.

399
00:36:32,730 --> 00:36:38,000

400
00:36:43,260 --> 00:36:45,700
Shall we go together?

401
00:36:54,360 --> 00:36:56,840
Shall we die together?

402
00:37:01,990 --> 00:37:04,220
I said I would be with you...

403
00:37:05,900 --> 00:37:08,690
until the very end.

404
00:37:14,280 --> 00:37:17,350
I don't think I can live without you.

405
00:37:19,090 --> 00:37:21,760
I don't want to do that anymore.

406
00:37:21,760 --> 00:37:24,360
Can't you wait for me?

407
00:37:25,030 --> 00:37:29,700
Could you not wait for me?

408
00:37:30,710 --> 00:37:32,680
Endure.

409
00:37:33,590 --> 00:37:35,790
Push it back.

410
00:37:36,930 --> 00:37:39,400
Can't you live?

411
00:37:47,510 --> 00:37:50,770
I don't want to get my hopes up anymore.

412
00:37:50,770 --> 00:37:53,610
I don't want to get greedy.

413
00:37:54,700 --> 00:37:56,670
I'm scared.

414
00:37:58,660 --> 00:38:01,230
Be greedy.

415
00:38:01,230 --> 00:38:03,730
Get your hopes up and walk.

416
00:38:04,960 --> 00:38:08,920
One year... One month.

417
00:38:10,280 --> 00:38:13,640
No, even if you can live for just one more day.

418
00:38:13,640 --> 00:38:16,560
Get the surgery, okay?

419
00:38:16,560 --> 00:38:19,120
Let's try whatever we can.

420
00:38:21,630 --> 00:38:24,030
So that I can be by your side...

421
00:38:25,510 --> 00:38:28,440
until the very end.

422
00:38:30,170 --> 00:38:32,800
Can't you do that for me?

423
00:39:21,440 --> 00:39:24,160
I will wait.

424
00:39:24,160 --> 00:39:26,530
I'm going to wait.

425
00:39:27,530 --> 00:39:29,640
Whatever it takes.

426
00:39:32,230 --> 00:39:34,340
I will wait.

