00:42:39,800 --> 00:42:41,600
Your son visited you thanks to that.

454
00:42:41,600 --> 00:42:43,560
Now you can go to the US,

455
00:42:43,560 --> 00:42:45,130
and with your son by your side...

456
00:42:45,130 --> 00:42:47,800
I can die next to him.

457
00:42:47,800 --> 00:42:50,490
Gosh, you can't just go like that.

458
00:42:50,490 --> 00:42:54,220
- I have to pay you back. 
 - Gosh!

459
00:42:54,220 --> 00:42:56,840
What need for money would I have now?

460
00:42:56,840 --> 00:43:00,720
It's all good for me now.

461
00:43:00,720 --> 00:43:02,990
The fact that things played out this way at the very end of my life...

462
00:43:02,990 --> 00:43:05,120
you have no idea how glad I am.

463
00:43:05,120 --> 00:43:10,440
Gosh, you should be thanking Mi Do. Here she comes right on time. Mi Do!

464
00:43:19,740 --> 00:43:21,370
How are you today?

465
00:43:21,370 --> 00:43:23,420
I'm good.

466
00:43:23,420 --> 00:43:27,460
Good. You'll get even better.

467
00:43:27,460 --> 00:43:31,650
Mi Do, thank you so much.

468
00:43:31,650 --> 00:43:32,830
I didn't do anything.

469
00:43:32,830 --> 00:43:37,500
Who would've known I would shine at the end of my life?

470
00:43:37,500 --> 00:43:40,830
I hit the jackpot thanks to you.

471
00:43:42,030 --> 00:43:45,820
But you gave all the money to In Sook instead.

472
00:43:46,430 --> 00:43:49,430
Thank you...

473
00:43:49,430 --> 00:43:51,900
for giving me the surgery money.

474
00:43:51,900 --> 00:43:56,110
If you're really grateful, you better make the money worth it.

475
00:43:56,110 --> 00:44:00,510
You have to live. You have to get better, all right?

476
00:44:05,650 --> 00:44:08,330
You are not dead,

477
00:44:08,330 --> 00:44:10,840
until you die.

478
00:44:10,840 --> 00:44:13,120
What are you saying?

479
00:44:14,440 --> 00:44:16,170
I'm just saying.

480
00:44:16,170 --> 00:44:20,440
What's up with you? Why are about to cry after saying something strange?

481
00:44:20,440 --> 00:44:23,780
It's because I can't do anything for you.

482
00:44:31,010 --> 00:44:36,230
- But where is Se Yeon? 
 - What?

483
00:44:36,230 --> 00:44:39,400
She was here just a moment ago.

484
00:44:39,400 --> 00:44:42,550
Where is Se Yeon?

485
00:44:44,770 --> 00:44:47,200
She...

486
00:44:47,200 --> 00:44:49,430
died.

487
00:44:49,430 --> 00:44:51,730
What are you saying?

488
00:44:52,540 --> 00:44:55,380
Gosh, what's wrong with you?

489
00:44:55,380 --> 00:44:58,600
Why are you being like this?

490
00:45:01,920 --> 00:45:07,290
You really can't remember? You can't remember Se Yeon's last day?

491
00:45:07,290 --> 00:45:09,920
We went to the beach together.

492
00:45:10,960 --> 00:45:14,790
Remember it! Try to remember it.

493
00:45:14,790 --> 00:45:17,360
Are you going to forget me, too?

494
00:45:17,360 --> 00:45:19,370
You have to remember.

495
00:45:19,370 --> 00:45:25,100
You have to survive and remember me after I die.

496
00:45:27,470 --> 00:45:30,840
I will remember.

497
00:45:30,840 --> 00:45:33,330
What about the first time we met?

498
00:45:33,330 --> 00:45:36,210
Do you remember the first time we met?

499
00:45:39,530 --> 00:45:42,540
We fought here.

500
00:45:42,540 --> 00:45:43,510
That's right.

501
00:45:43,510 --> 00:45:48,610
What about the time you went to go save San Ah?

502
00:45:50,570 --> 00:45:54,890
What about Woo Cheon then? You don't remember him?

503
00:45:59,890 --> 00:46:01,940
I remember him.

504
00:46:04,220 --> 00:46:06,380
I will remember.

