509
00:46:27,460 --> 00:46:31,160
That means I can get better, right?

510
00:46:31,160 --> 00:46:34,590
They tried to remove the brain tumor as much as they could.

511
00:46:34,590 --> 00:46:40,490
But part of the temporal lobe is related to language, so they couldn't remove everything.

512
00:46:40,490 --> 00:46:43,630
That may be why you're experiencing memory loss.

513
00:46:43,630 --> 00:46:48,420
Are you saying I'll lose more of my memory over time?

514
00:46:48,420 --> 00:46:53,490
We'll have to keep an eye on your condition and get a diagnosis from the hospital.

515
00:46:53,490 --> 00:46:58,370
What is left behind if I lose my memory?

516
00:46:58,370 --> 00:47:01,140
What do I have to do? What can I do?

517
00:47:01,140 --> 00:47:05,080
There's an old saying in Russian.

518
00:47:05,080 --> 00:47:07,700
Pray to God.

519
00:47:07,700 --> 00:47:12,250
But don't stop moving your hand

520
00:47:12,250 --> 00:47:14,910
that is rowing towards the land.

521
00:47:38,090 --> 00:47:43,210
You still carry on living.

522
00:48:03,740 --> 00:48:06,620
 I was like an alley cat.

523
00:48:08,660 --> 00:48:10,710
 Hey, come at me! Try me!

524
00:48:10,710 --> 00:48:12,180
 - Even if you die? 
 - Let go!

525
00:48:12,180 --> 00:48:14,890
 What are you doing? You're a shameless thief!

526
00:48:14,890 --> 00:48:17,360
 They say the reason why alley cats have their guard up so much...

527
